This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the modeling of language use and communication. The paper also involves computational simulations, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data from the TUNA corpus, which is related to natural language processing and could place it in the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). Finally, the paper involves modeling and simulations, which could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
